1.Mistake in my find_index function
return -1 is inside the for loop
Current structure:
for value in list:
    if value == target:
        return i   # OK
    return -1      #  This executes on the first iteration
Effect of the mistake:
The function checks only the first item.
If the first item is not the target, it immediately returns -1, without checking the rest of the list.
Conceptual error:
You’re signaling “not found” too early.
“Not found” should only be concluded after checking all items, not after the first one.

